

Difference b/w Interface & Abstract Class
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	# Interface
		- Object cannot be instantiated
		- All methods in interface are public & cannot be implemented
		- Multiple Interface can be implemented
	# Abstract Class
		- Methods can have implementation, but the object cannot be instantiated
		- Only one Abstract class can be extended at a time

Cloning
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	
	# Shallow cloning wll retain the non-primitive type reference in both the objects
		- Deep cloning is needed to avoid this issue 
		- In order to clone an object(Shallow or Deep) we should implement 'Cloneable' interface
	# http://howtodoinjava.com/2012/11/08/a-guide-to-object-cloning-in-java/
	

Serializable
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	# Is a Marker Interface. A Market Interface do not contain any fields or methods
	# http://javatechig.com/design-patterns/singleton-design-pattern-in-java
	
Singleton
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	# Cloning can be avoided by implementing the 'Cloneable' interface and 
	  overriding the 'clone()' method to throw 'CloneNotSupported' Exception
	# http://javatechig.com/design-patterns/singleton-design-pattern-in-java
	